title: Auroral Images, Key Parameters, IMAGE Far UltraViolet (FUV) Wide-band Imaging Camera (WIC) - S. Mende (UC/Berkeley/SSL)

info.x_cadence_note: Counts based on variable 'EPOCH' in https://cdaweb.gsfc.nasa.gov/sp_phys/data/image/fuv/wic_k0/2000/im_k0_wic_20000425_v01.cdf. The most common cadence occurred for 6.2500% of the 1 timesteps. Cadence = 248393 [ms] = PT4M8.393S.

parameters.name: WIC_PIXELS
parameters.description: FUV/WIC LBH Auroral Images (raw cnts/14 bits, no grid, small format, linear scale)

parameters.name: WIC_PIXELS_LARGE
parameters.description: ---> FUV/WIC LBH Auroral Images, as above (large format). This variable is a 'virtual' variable that is computed using the function alternate_view (see https://cdaweb.gsfc.nasa.gov/pub/software/cdawlib/source/virtual_funcs.pro) on the with inputs of the variables ['WIC_PIXELS']. Note that some COMPONENTS may not be available from the HAPI interface. They are accessible from the raw CDF files, however.

parameters.description: WIC Quality parameter (1=Good, 2=Bad)
